    "body": "Sometimes, sites hosting software can go down. And this can throw a monkey wrench into an install.  One solution to this (in the works, I believe) is to cache tarballs.  Another approach, is for Spack to allow for more than one way to download a tarball.  Spack would then try all the alternates until it finds one that works.\n\nWithout that, we end up with things like PR #1089 \n",
